description: From Medieval Latin paginare, from Latin pagina.

verbs.description: paginate (third-person singular simple present paginates, present participle paginating, simple past and past participle paginated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To number the pages of (a book or other document); to foliate.
(transitive, computing) To separate (data) into batches, so that it can be retrieved with a number of smaller requests.
